{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01FTnP5t3SWhFhM4pdgo1gKC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base}\n     2→{#body}\n     3→<h2>\n     4→    {#if !visit}{msg:new_} {/if}\n     5→    {msg:visit}\n     6→</h2>\n     7→\n     8→<b>Pet</b>\n     9→<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    10→    <thead>\n    11→        <tr>\n    12→            <th>{msg:name}</th>\n    13→            <th>{msg:birthdate}</th>\n    14→            <th>{msg:type}</th>\n    15→            <th>{msg:owner}</th>\n    16→        </tr>\n    17→    </thead>\n    18→    <tr>\n    19→        <td>{pet.name}</td>\n    20→        <td>{pet.birthDate.format()}</td>\n    21→        <td>{pet.type.name}</td>\n    22→        <td>{pet.owner.firstName} {pet.owner.lastName}</td>\n    23→    </tr>\n    24→</table>\n    25→\n    26→<form class=\"form-horizontal\" method=\"post\">\n    27→    <div class=\"form-group has-feedback\">\n    28→\n    29→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    30→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:date}</label>\n    31→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    32→                <div>\n    33→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" placeholder=\"YYYY-MM-DD\"\n    34→                        id=\"date\" name=\"date\" value=\"{visit.date ?: ''}\"/>\n    35→                </div>\n    36→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    37→                {#if errors.containsKey('date') != null}\n    38→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('date')}</span>\n    39→                {/if}\n    40→            </div>\n    41→        </div>\n    42→\n    43→\n    44→        <div class=\"form-group {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null} has-error {/if}\">\n    45→            <label class=\"col-sm-2 control-label\">{msg:description}</label>\n    46→            <div class=\"col-sm-10\">\n    47→                <div>\n    48→                    <input class=\"form-control\" type=\"text\" id=\"description\" name=\"description\" value=\"{visit.description ?: ''}\" />\n    49→                </div>\n    50→                <span class=\"glyphicon {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null} glyphicon-remove {#else} glyphicon-ok {/if} form-control-feedback\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    51→                {#if errors.containsKey('description') != null}\n    52→                    <span class=\"help-inline\">{errors.containsKey('description')}</span>\n    53→                {/if}\n    54→            </div>\n    55→        </div>\n    56→\n    57→    </div>\n    58→\n    59→    <div class=\"form-group\">\n    60→        <div class=\"col-sm-offset-2 col-sm-10\">\n    61→            <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"petId\" value=\"1\" />\n    62→            <button class=\"btn btn-primary\" type=\"submit\">{msg:add_visit}</button>\n    63→        </div>\n    64→    </div>\n    65→</form>\n    66→\n    67→<br />\n    68→<b>{msg:previous_visits}</b>\n    69→<table class=\"table table-striped\">\n    70→    <tr>\n    71→        <th>{msg:date}</th>\n    72→        <th>{msg:description}</th>\n    73→    </tr>\n    74→    <tr>\n    75→        {#if visit}\n    76→        {#for v in pet.sortedVisits}\n    77→        <td>{v.date.format()}</td>\n    78→        <td>{v.description}</td>\n    79→        {/for}\n    80→        {/if}\n    81→    </tr>\n    82→</table>\n    83→{/body}\n    84→{/include}\n    85→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"7bef33f4-3b17-4486-b40a-3d715b805062"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01XtkwbDFPdoMeAr52jps8VA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{#include base} \n     2→  {#body}\n     3→  <h2>{msg:welcome}</h2>\n     4→  <div class=\"row\">\n     5→      <div class=\"col-md-12\">\n     6→        <img class=\"img-responsive\" src=\"../images/pets.png\"/>\n     7→        <h2>{msg:error}</h2>\n     8→        <p>{msg:something_wrong}</p>\n     9→      </div>\n    10→  </div>\n    11→  {/body}\n    12→{/include}\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"67237380-799a-4bcf-9852-80200e510871"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014h8AVo4EjrVKwdk2gFDpFh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a complete picture of the application. Let me now execute the migration. The key design decisions are:\n\n**Migration Strategy:**\n- Replace Quarkus with a standard Jakarta EE thin WAR running on **WildFly Bootable JAR** (embeds the server in a single JAR)\n- Replace Panache with standard JPA/Hibernate EntityManager\n- Replace Qute templates with **JSP** (standard Jakarta EE server-side rendering)\n- Keep JAX-RS (Jakarta REST) as-is (already using `jakarta.ws.rs` APIs)\n- Keep JPA annotations (already using `jakarta.persistence`)\n- Keep CDI (already using `jakarta.inject`)\n- Keep Bean Validation (already using `jakarta.validation`)\n- Replace Qute i18n with simple Java class that provides message strings\n\nLet me now execute all the file changes. I'll use multiple parallel agents for efficiency:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8432,"cache_read_input_tokens":48624,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8432,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2125},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"f353c62b-57c8-453c-ac41-6cc872320948"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_014h8AVo4EjrVKwdk2gFDpFh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_013AmdMBRr2N9hqH9Bw3zWXY","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Write new pom.xml for WildFly","prompt":"Write a new pom.xml file at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/pom.xml\n\nThis is migrating from Quarkus to a standard Jakarta EE application running on WildFly Bootable JAR. The application is a PetClinic web app using:\n- JAX-RS (Jakarta REST) for REST endpoints\n- JPA (Hibernate) for database access  \n- CDI for dependency injection\n- Bean Validation\n- JSP for server-side templating (replacing Qute)\n- H2 database (embedded for dev mode)\n- Jackson for JSON serialization\n- WebJars for Bootstrap and Font Awesome\n\nWrite the COMPLETE pom.xml with these requirements:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n    xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n  <groupId>org.quarkus.samples.petclinic</groupId>\n  <artifactId>jakarta-petclinic</artifactId>\n  <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n  <packaging>war</packaging>\n  <properties>\n    <maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>\n    <maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>\n    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    <jakarta.jakartaee-api.version>10.0.0</jakarta.jakartaee-api.version>\n    <wildfly.version>35.0.1.Final</wildfly.version>\n    <wildfly-maven-plugin.version>5.1.2.Final</wildfly-maven-plugin.version>\n    <wildfly-datasources.version>8.0.1.Final</wildfly-datasources.version>\n    <webjars-bootstrap.version>5.1.3</webjars-bootstrap.version>\n    <webjars-font-awesome.version>4.7.0</webjars-font-awesome.version>\n    <compiler-plugin.version>3.14.0</compiler-plugin.version>\n    <war-plugin.version>3.4.0</war-plugin.version>\n  </properties>\n  <dependencies>\n    <!-- Jakarta EE API -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-api</artifactId>\n      <version>${jakarta.jakartaee-api.version}</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Jackson for JSON -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jackson-databind</artifactId>\n      <version>2.17.2</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jackson-annotations</artifactId>\n      <version>2.17.2</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- JBoss Logging - provided by WildFly -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.jboss.logging</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jboss-logging</artifactId>\n      <version>3.6.1.Final</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Webjars -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.webjars.npm</groupId>\n      <artifactId>bootstrap</artifactId>\n      <version>${webjars-bootstrap.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.webjars.npm</groupId>\n      <artifactId>font-awesome</artifactId>\n      <version>${webjars-font-awesome.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n    <!-- WebJars Servlet -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.webjars</groupId>\n      <artifactId>webjars-servlet-2.x</artifactId>\n      <version>1.6</version>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- JSTL for JSP -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.glassfish.web</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl</artifactId>\n      <version>3.0.1</version>\n    </dependency>\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl-api</artifactId>\n      <version>3.0.2</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n  </dependencies>\n  <build>\n    <finalName>petclinic</finalName>\n    <plugins>\n      <plugin>\n        <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n        <version>${compiler-plugin.version}</version>\n        <configuration>\n          <source>21</source>\n          <target>21</target>\n        </configuration>\n      </plugin>\n      <plugin>\n        <artifactId>maven-war-plugin</artifactId>\n        <version>${war-plugin.version}</version>\n        <configuration>\n          <failOnMissingWebXml>false</failOnMissingWebXml>\n        </configuration>\n      </plugin>\n      <plugin>\n        <groupId>org.wildfly.plugins</groupId>\n        <artifactId>wildfly-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n        <version>${wildfly-maven-plugin.version}</version>\n        <configuration>\n          <feature-packs>\n            <feature-pack>\n              <location>org.wildfly:wildfly-galleon-pack:${wildfly.version}</location>\n            </feature-pack>\n            <feature-pack>\n              <location>org.wildfly:wildfly-datasources-galleon-pack:${wildfly-datasources.version}</location>\n            </feature-pack>\n          </feature-packs>\n          <layers>\n            <layer>cloud-server</layer>\n            <layer>h2-default-datasource</layer>\n          </layers>\n          <runtime-name>ROOT.war</runtime-name>\n          <packaging-scripts>\n            <packaging-script>\n              <scripts>\n                <script>configure-server.cli</script>\n              </scripts>\n            </packaging-script>\n          </packaging-scripts>\n        </configuration>\n        <executions>\n          <execution>\n            <goals>\n              <goal>package</goal>\n            </goals>\n          </execution>\n        </executions>\n      </plugin>\n    </plugins>\n  </build>\n</project>\n```\n\nUse the Write tool to write this exact content to the pom.xml file.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8432,"cache_read_input_tokens":48624,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8432,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2125},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"93eb681b-fa5d-44f0-8904-5746208ca86f"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write a new pom.xml file at:\n/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/pom.xml\n\nThis is migrating from Quarkus to a standard Jakarta EE application running on WildFly Bootable JAR. The application is a PetClinic web app using:\n- JAX-RS (Jakarta REST) for REST endpoints\n- JPA (Hibernate) for database access  \n- CDI for dependency injection\n- Bean Validation\n- JSP for server-side templating (replacing Qute)\n- H2 database (embedded for dev mode)\n- Jackson for JSON serialization\n- WebJars for Bootstrap and Font Awesome\n\nWrite the COMPLETE pom.xml with these requirements:\n\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<project xmlns=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"\n    xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 https://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd\">\n  <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>\n  <groupId>org.quarkus.samples.petclinic</groupId>\n  <artifactId>jakarta-petclinic</artifactId>\n  <version>1.0.0-SNAPSHOT</version>\n  <packaging>war</packaging>\n  <properties>\n    <maven.compiler.source>21</maven.compiler.source>\n    <maven.compiler.target>21</maven.compiler.target>\n    <project.build.sourceEncoding>UTF-8</project.build.sourceEncoding>\n    <jakarta.jakartaee-api.version>10.0.0</jakarta.jakartaee-api.version>\n    <wildfly.version>35.0.1.Final</wildfly.version>\n    <wildfly-maven-plugin.version>5.1.2.Final</wildfly-maven-plugin.version>\n    <wildfly-datasources.version>8.0.1.Final</wildfly-datasources.version>\n    <webjars-bootstrap.version>5.1.3</webjars-bootstrap.version>\n    <webjars-font-awesome.version>4.7.0</webjars-font-awesome.version>\n    <compiler-plugin.version>3.14.0</compiler-plugin.version>\n    <war-plugin.version>3.4.0</war-plugin.version>\n  </properties>\n  <dependencies>\n    <!-- Jakarta EE API -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>jakarta.platform</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jakarta.jakartaee-api</artifactId>\n      <version>${jakarta.jakartaee-api.version}</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Jackson for JSON -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jackson-databind</artifactId>\n      <version>2.17.2</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>com.fasterxml.jackson.core</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jackson-annotations</artifactId>\n      <version>2.17.2</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- JBoss Logging - provided by WildFly -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.jboss.logging</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jboss-logging</artifactId>\n      <version>3.6.1.Final</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- Webjars -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.webjars.npm</groupId>\n      <artifactId>bootstrap</artifactId>\n      <version>${webjars-bootstrap.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.webjars.npm</groupId>\n      <artifactId>font-awesome</artifactId>\n      <version>${webjars-font-awesome.version}</version>\n    </dependency>\n    <!-- WebJars Servlet -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.webjars</groupId>\n      <artifactId>webjars-servlet-2.x</artifactId>\n      <version>1.6</version>\n    </dependency>\n\n    <!-- JSTL for JSP -->\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>org.glassfish.web</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl</artifactId>\n      <version>3.0.1</version>\n    </dependency>\n    <dependency>\n      <groupId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl</groupId>\n      <artifactId>jakarta.servlet.jsp.jstl-api</artifactId>\n      <version>3.0.2</version>\n      <scope>provided</scope>\n    </dependency>\n  </dependencies>\n  <build>\n    <finalName>petclinic</finalName>\n    <plugins>\n      <plugin>\n        <artifactId>maven-compiler-plugin</artifactId>\n        <version>${compiler-plugin.version}</version>\n        <configuration>\n          <source>21</source>\n          <target>21</target>\n        </configuration>\n      </plugin>\n      <plugin>\n        <artifactId>maven-war-plugin</artifactId>\n        <version>${war-plugin.version}</version>\n        <configuration>\n          <failOnMissingWebXml>false</failOnMissingWebXml>\n        </configuration>\n      </plugin>\n      <plugin>\n        <groupId>org.wildfly.plugins</groupId>\n        <artifactId>wildfly-maven-plugin</artifactId>\n        <version>${wildfly-maven-plugin.version}</version>\n        <configuration>\n          <feature-packs>\n            <feature-pack>\n              <location>org.wildfly:wildfly-galleon-pack:${wildfly.version}</location>\n            </feature-pack>\n            <feature-pack>\n              <location>org.wildfly:wildfly-datasources-galleon-pack:${wildfly-datasources.version}</location>\n            </feature-pack>\n          </feature-packs>\n          <layers>\n            <layer>cloud-server</layer>\n            <layer>h2-default-datasource</layer>\n          </layers>\n          <runtime-name>ROOT.war</runtime-name>\n          <packaging-scripts>\n            <packaging-script>\n              <scripts>\n                <script>configure-server.cli</script>\n              </scripts>\n            </packaging-script>\n          </packaging-scripts>\n        </configuration>\n        <executions>\n          <execution>\n            <goals>\n              <goal>package</goal>\n            </goals>\n          </execution>\n        </executions>\n      </plugin>\n    </plugins>\n  </build>\n</project>\n```\n\nUse the Write tool to write this exact content to the pom.xml file."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013AmdMBRr2N9hqH9Bw3zWXY","session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"719c5567-e775-46e0-b8e2-b86f4a4ccb55"}
