{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_013AmdMBRr2N9hqH9Bw3zWXY","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully written the new pom.xml file for the Jakarta EE migration. \n\n## Summary\n\nThe pom.xml file has been successfully created at:\n**`/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/pom.xml`**\n\nThis new Maven configuration migrates the PetClinic application from Quarkus to a standard Jakarta EE application running on WildFly Bootable JAR. Key changes include:\n\n### Major Changes:\n1. **Packaging**: Changed from JAR to `war` (Web Application Archive)\n2. **Artifact ID**: Changed from `quarkus-petclinic` to `jakarta-petclinic`\n3. **Dependencies**: Replaced Quarkus-specific dependencies with Jakarta EE 10 APIs\n4. **Build Configuration**: Replaced Quarkus Maven Plugin with WildFly Maven Plugin\n\n### Key Dependencies:\n- Jakarta EE 10 API (provided scope)\n- Jackson for JSON processing (provided by WildFly)\n- JBoss Logging (provided by WildFly)\n- Bootstrap 5.1.3 and Font Awesome 4.7.0 via WebJars\n- JSTL for JSP templating support\n\n### Build Configuration:\n- WildFly 35.0.1.Final as the application server\n- H2 datasource layer for embedded database\n- Cloud-server layer for lightweight deployment\n- Configured to build a bootable JAR with embedded WildFly\n- References a `configure-server.cli` script for additional server configuration\n\nThe configuration maintains the same Java 21 source/target and UTF-8 encoding as the original Quarkus project."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"fafdf865-ce12-4a65-bf4b-9db8570bd9cd"}
