{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018uLPMtMPjmVTLtxFgD4Eo4","type":"tool_result","content":"<!doctype html>\n<html>\n<head>\n  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\" />\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n  <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n  <title>PetClinic :: a Jakarta EE demonstration</title>\n  <link rel=\"shortcut icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"/petclinic/images/favicon.ico\">\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/petclinic/webjars/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\">\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/petclinic/css/petclinic.css\" />\n</head>\n<body>\n  <nav class=\"navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark\" role=\"navigation\">\n    <div class=\"container\">\n      <div class=\"navbar-header\">\n        <a class=\"navbar-brand\" href=\"/petclinic/\"><span></span></a>\n        <button class=\"navbar-toggler\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#main-navbar\">\n          <span class=\"navbar-toggler-icon\"></span>\n        </button>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"collapse navbar-collapse\" id=\"main-navbar\" style>\n        <ul class=\"nav navbar-nav me-auto\">\n          <li class=\"active\">\n            <a href=\"/petclinic/\" title=\"home page\">\n              <span class=\"fa fa-home\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n              <span>Home</span>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"d29b436c-1473-4c00-8ab5-057af1587196"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01SiGh9ywURixdVTkdQTc2Nh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The app is running at `/petclinic/app/`. The context path is `/petclinic` (from the WAR name). I need to either:\n1. Deploy as ROOT.war to get context path `/`\n2. Or update the smoke tests to use the right context path\n\nThe simplest fix is to rename the WAR to ROOT.war in the build. Let me also fix the JSP header.jsp to use `${pageContext.request.contextPath}/app/` consistently. But first, let me test the current state more:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":891,"cache_read_input_tokens":152939,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":891,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":330},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"82d61b33-b5ef-4777-bb75-03b9525168e9"}
