{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01SuKVTAKCvV6cKB565c43Mb","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→<%@ page contentType=\"text/html;charset=UTF-8\" language=\"java\" %>\n     2→<%@ taglib prefix=\"c\" uri=\"jakarta.tags.core\" %>\n     3→<!doctype html>\n     4→<html>\n     5→<head>\n     6→  <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\" />\n     7→  <meta charset=\"utf-8\">\n     8→  <meta http-equiv=\"X-UA-Compatible\" content=\"IE=edge\">\n     9→  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1\">\n    10→  <title>PetClinic :: a Jakarta EE Framework demonstration</title>\n    11→  <link rel=\"shortcut icon\" type=\"image/x-icon\" href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/images/favicon.ico\">\n    12→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/webjars/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css\">\n    13→  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/css/petclinic.css\" />\n    14→</head>\n    15→<body>\n    16→  <nav class=\"navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark\" role=\"navigation\">\n    17→    <div class=\"container\">\n    18→      <div class=\"navbar-header\">\n    19→        <a class=\"navbar-brand\" href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/app/\"><span></span></a>\n    20→        <button class=\"navbar-toggler\" type=\"button\" data-bs-toggle=\"collapse\" data-bs-target=\"#main-navbar\">\n    21→          <span class=\"navbar-toggler-icon\"></span>\n    22→        </button>\n    23→      </div>\n    24→      <div class=\"collapse navbar-collapse\" id=\"main-navbar\" style>\n    25→        <ul class=\"nav navbar-nav me-auto\">\n    26→          <li class=\"active\">\n    27→            <a href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/app/\" title=\"home page\">\n    28→              <span class=\"fa fa-home\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    29→              <span>Home</span>\n    30→            </a>\n    31→          </li>\n    32→          <li>\n    33→            <a href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/app/owners/find\" title=\"find owners\">\n    34→              <span class=\"fa fa-search\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    35→              <span>Find Owners</span>\n    36→            </a>\n    37→          </li>\n    38→          <li>\n    39→            <a href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/app/vets.html\" title=\"veterinarians\">\n    40→              <span class=\"fa fa-th-list\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    41→              <span>Veterinarians</span>\n    42→            </a>\n    43→          </li>\n    44→          <li>\n    45→            <a href=\"${pageContext.request.contextPath}/app/oups\" title=\"trigger a RuntimeException to see how it is handled\">\n    46→              <span class=\"fa exclamation-triangle\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></span>\n    47→              <span>Error</span>\n    48→            </a>\n    49→          </li>\n    50→        </ul>\n    51→      </div>\n    52→    </div>\n    53→  </nav>\n    54→  <div class=\"container-fluid\">\n    55→    <div class=\"container xd-container\">\n    56→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"008bf01e-c3f9-418c-9049-ace99d65b975"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01G3NviBoGHPhjYeP43LFDE9","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ws.rs.ApplicationPath;\n     4→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Application;\n     5→\n     6→@ApplicationPath(\"/app\")\n     7→public class JaxRsApplication extends Application {\n     8→}\n     9→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"b584f603-a3ad-4a2f-8bd9-6d4756a14472"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01PTuWUJvLLhvriaFv9HrWQR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     6→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n     7→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n     8→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n     9→import jakarta.transaction.Transactional;\n    10→import jakarta.validation.ConstraintViolation;\n    11→import jakarta.validation.Validator;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Consumes;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.FormParam;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    15→import jakarta.ws.rs.POST;\n    16→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    17→import jakarta.ws.rs.PathParam;\n    18→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    19→import jakarta.ws.rs.QueryParam;\n    20→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    21→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    22→import org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    23→\n    24→import java.io.IOException;\n    25→import java.util.Arrays;\n    26→import java.util.Collection;\n    27→import java.util.Collections;\n    28→import java.util.HashMap;\n    29→import java.util.List;\n    30→import java.util.Map;\n    31→import java.util.Set;\n    32→\n    33→@Path(\"/owners\")\n    34→public class OwnersResource {\n    35→\n    36→    @PersistenceContext\n    37→    EntityManager em;\n    38→\n    39→    @Inject\n    40→    Validator validator;\n    41→\n    42→    @Context\n    43→    private HttpServletRequest request;\n    44→\n    45→    @Context\n    46→    private HttpServletResponse response;\n    47→\n    48→    @GET\n    49→    @Path(\"/find\")\n    50→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    51→    public void findTemplate() throws ServletException, IOException {\n    52→        request.setAttribute(\"errors\", Collections.emptyList());\n    53→        request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/findOwners.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    @GET\n    57→    @Path(\"new\")\n    58→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    59→    public void createTemplate() throws ServletException, IOException {\n    60→        request.setAttribute(\"owner\", null);\n    61→        request.setAttribute(\"errors\", new HashMap<>());\n    62→        request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    @GET\n    66→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/edit\")\n    67→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    68→    public void editTemplate(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    69→        Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    70→        request.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n    71→        request.setAttribute(\"errors\", new HashMap<>());\n    72→        request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    @GET\n    76→    @Path(\"{ownerId}\")\n    77→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    78→    public void showOwner(@PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    79→        Owner owner = em.find(Owner.class, ownerId);\n    80→        setVisits(owner);\n    81→        request.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n    82→        request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    @POST\n    86→    @Path(\"new\")\n    87→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    88→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n    89→    @Transactional\n    90→    public void processCreationForm(@FormParam(\"firstName\") String firstName,\n    91→                                    @FormParam(\"lastName\") String lastName,\n    92→                                    @FormParam(\"address\") String address,\n    93→                                    @FormParam(\"city\") String city,\n    94→                                    @FormParam(\"telephone\") String telephone) throws ServletException, IOException {\n    95→        Owner owner = new Owner();\n    96→        owner.firstName = firstName;\n    97→        owner.lastName = lastName;\n    98→        owner.address = address;\n    99→        owner.city = city;\n   100→        owner.telephone = telephone;\n   101→\n   102→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   103→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   104→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   105→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   106→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   107→            }\n   108→            request.setAttribute(\"owner\", null);\n   109→            request.setAttribute(\"errors\", errors);\n   110→            request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n   111→        } else {\n   112→            em.persist(owner);\n   113→            em.flush();\n   114→            setVisits(owner);\n   115→            request.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   116→            request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n   117→        }\n   118→    }\n   119→\n   120→    @POST\n   121→    @Path(\"{ownerId}/edit\")\n   122→    @Consumes(MediaType.APPLICATION_FORM_URLENCODED)\n   123→    @Transactional\n   124→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   125→    public void processUpdateOwnerForm(@FormParam(\"firstName\") String firstName,\n   126→                                       @FormParam(\"lastName\") String lastName,\n   127→                                       @FormParam(\"address\") String address,\n   128→                                       @FormParam(\"city\") String city,\n   129→                                       @FormParam(\"telephone\") String telephone,\n   130→                                       @PathParam(\"ownerId\") Long ownerId) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   131→        Owner owner = new Owner();\n   132→        owner.id = ownerId;\n   133→        owner.firstName = firstName;\n   134→        owner.lastName = lastName;\n   135→        owner.address = address;\n   136→        owner.city = city;\n   137→        owner.telephone = telephone;\n   138→\n   139→        final Set<ConstraintViolation<Owner>> violations = validator.validate(owner);\n   140→        final Map<String, String> errors = new HashMap<>();\n   141→        if (!violations.isEmpty()) {\n   142→            for (ConstraintViolation<Owner> violation : violations) {\n   143→                errors.put(violation.getPropertyPath().toString(), violation.getMessage());\n   144→            }\n   145→            request.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   146→            request.setAttribute(\"errors\", errors);\n   147→            request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/createOrUpdateOwnerForm.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n   148→        } else {\n   149→            Owner merged = em.merge(owner);\n   150→            setVisits(merged);\n   151→            request.setAttribute(\"owner\", merged);\n   152→            request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n   153→        }\n   154→    }\n   155→\n   156→    @GET\n   157→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n   158→    public void processFindForm(@QueryParam(\"lastName\") String lastName) throws ServletException, IOException {\n   159→        List<Owner> owners;\n   160→\n   161→        if (lastName == null || \"\".equals(lastName.trim())) {\n   162→            owners = em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o\", Owner.class).getResultList();\n   163→        } else {\n   164→            owners = em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o WHERE o.lastName = :lastName\", Owner.class)\n   165→                    .setParameter(\"lastName\", lastName)\n   166→                    .getResultList();\n   167→        }\n   168→\n   169→        if (owners.isEmpty()) {\n   170→            request.setAttribute(\"errors\", Arrays.asList(\"lastName not found\"));\n   171→            request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/findOwners.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n   172→            return;\n   173→        }\n   174→        if (owners.size() == 1) {\n   175→            Owner owner = owners.get(0);\n   176→            setVisits(owner);\n   177→            request.setAttribute(\"owner\", owner);\n   178→            request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownerDetails.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n   179→            return;\n   180→        }\n   181→\n   182→        request.setAttribute(\"owners\", owners);\n   183→        request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/ownersList.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n   184→    }\n   185→\n   186→    protected void setVisits(Owner owner) {\n   187→        if (owner != null && owner.pets != null) {\n   188→            for (Pet pet : owner.pets) {\n   189→                List<Visit> visits = em.createQuery(\"SELECT v FROM Visit v WHERE v.petId = :petId\", Visit.class)\n   190→                        .setParameter(\"petId\", pet.id)\n   191→                        .getResultList();\n   192→                pet.setVisitsInternal(visits);\n   193→            }\n   194→        }\n   195→    }\n   196→\n   197→    @Path(\"/api/list\")\n   198→    @GET\n   199→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n   200→    public List<Owner> listOwners() {\n   201→        return em.createQuery(\"SELECT o FROM Owner o\", Owner.class).getResultList();\n   202→    }\n   203→}\n   204→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"2db82d42-bf54-4330-baae-db01578fbb61"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01QD7Dn3nSq9fnCdfhP4sikq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Good. Now I understand the URL structure. With ROOT.war deployed at `/`, all JAX-RS endpoints are at `/app/...`. The smoke tests need to use `/app/` as the prefix. Let me update the smoke tests to use the proper URL paths:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4788,"cache_read_input_tokens":39877,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4788,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2083},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"a9b6b362-9593-4f21-b391-d58dbf9d5bec"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01QD7Dn3nSq9fnCdfhP4sikq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01VCvPKPquydT8gxN9hgj64J","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/smoke.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nSmoke tests for the PetClinic application.\nTests the core functionality after migration from Quarkus to Jakarta EE.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport time\nimport requests\n\nBASE_URL = os.environ.get(\"BASE_URL\", \"http://localhost:8080\")\nAPP = \"/app\"\n\n\ndef url(path):\n    \"\"\"Build a full URL for the given path under the JAX-RS application root.\"\"\"\n    return f\"{BASE_URL}{APP}{path}\"\n\n\ndef test_welcome_page():\n    \"\"\"Test the welcome/home page loads.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Welcome page returned {r.status_code}\"\n    assert \"PetClinic\" in r.text or \"Welcome\" in r.text or \"welcome\" in r.text, \\\n        \"Welcome page missing expected content\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Welcome page loads correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_find_owners_page():\n    \"\"\"Test the find owners page loads.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/owners/find\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Find owners page returned {r.status_code}\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Find owners page loads correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_list_all_owners():\n    \"\"\"Test listing all owners.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/owners?lastName=\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"List owners returned {r.status_code}\"\n    assert \"George\" in r.text or \"Franklin\" in r.text, \\\n        \"Owner list missing expected owner data\"\n    print(\"[PASS] List all owners works correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_owner_details():\n    \"\"\"Test viewing owner details.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/owners/1001\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Owner details returned {r.status_code}\"\n    assert \"George\" in r.text or \"Franklin\" in r.text, \\\n        \"Owner details missing expected data\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Owner details page loads correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_vets_html_page():\n    \"\"\"Test the veterinarians HTML page.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/vets.html\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Vets HTML page returned {r.status_code}\"\n    assert \"James\" in r.text or \"Carter\" in r.text, \\\n        \"Vets page missing expected vet data\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Vets HTML page loads correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_vets_json_api():\n    \"\"\"Test the vets JSON API.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/vets\"), timeout=10, headers={\"Accept\": \"application/json\"})\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Vets API returned {r.status_code}\"\n    data = r.json()\n    assert \"vetList\" in data, \"Vets JSON missing vetList field\"\n    assert len(data[\"vetList\"]) > 0, \"Vets list is empty\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Vets JSON API works correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_owners_api():\n    \"\"\"Test the owners JSON API.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/owners/api/list\"), timeout=10,\n                     headers={\"Accept\": \"application/json\"})\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Owners API returned {r.status_code}\"\n    data = r.json()\n    assert len(data) > 0, \"Owners list is empty\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Owners JSON API works correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_new_owner_form():\n    \"\"\"Test the new owner form loads.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/owners/new\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"New owner form returned {r.status_code}\"\n    print(\"[PASS] New owner form loads correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_error_page():\n    \"\"\"Test the error page works.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/oups\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Error page returned {r.status_code}\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Error page works correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_create_owner():\n    \"\"\"Test creating a new owner via POST.\"\"\"\n    data = {\n        \"firstName\": \"TestFirst\",\n        \"lastName\": \"TestLast\",\n        \"address\": \"123 Test St\",\n        \"city\": \"TestCity\",\n        \"telephone\": \"1234567890\"\n    }\n    r = requests.post(url(\"/owners/new\"), data=data, timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"Create owner returned {r.status_code}\"\n    assert \"TestFirst\" in r.text or \"TestLast\" in r.text, \\\n        \"Created owner not shown in response\"\n    print(\"[PASS] Create new owner works correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_new_pet_form():\n    \"\"\"Test the new pet form loads for an existing owner.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/owners/1001/pets/new\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"New pet form returned {r.status_code}\"\n    print(\"[PASS] New pet form loads correctly\")\n\n\ndef test_new_visit_form():\n    \"\"\"Test the new visit form loads for an existing pet.\"\"\"\n    r = requests.get(url(\"/owners/1001/pets/1001/visits/new\"), timeout=10)\n    assert r.status_code == 200, f\"New visit form returned {r.status_code}\"\n    print(\"[PASS] New visit form loads correctly\")\n\n\ndef wait_for_server(base_url, timeout=120):\n    \"\"\"Wait for the server to become available.\"\"\"\n    start = time.time()\n    while time.time() - start < timeout:\n        try:\n            r = requests.get(f\"{base_url}/app/\", timeout=5)\n            if r.status_code < 500:\n                return True\n        except (requests.ConnectionError, requests.Timeout):\n            pass\n        time.sleep(2)\n    return False\n\n\ndef main():\n    print(f\"Running smoke tests against {BASE_URL}\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n\n    # Wait for server to be ready\n    print(\"Waiting for server to be ready...\")\n    if not wait_for_server(BASE_URL):\n        print(\"[FAIL] Server did not become available within timeout\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    print(\"Server is ready!\")\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n\n    tests = [\n        test_welcome_page,\n        test_find_owners_page,\n        test_list_all_owners,\n        test_owner_details,\n        test_vets_html_page,\n        test_vets_json_api,\n        test_owners_api,\n        test_new_owner_form,\n        test_error_page,\n        test_create_owner,\n        test_new_pet_form,\n        test_new_visit_form,\n    ]\n\n    passed = 0\n    failed = 0\n    errors = []\n\n    for test in tests:\n        try:\n            test()\n            passed += 1\n        except Exception as e:\n            failed += 1\n            errors.append(f\"[FAIL] {test.__name__}: {e}\")\n            print(f\"[FAIL] {test.__name__}: {e}\")\n\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\n    print(f\"Results: {passed} passed, {failed} failed out of {len(tests)} tests\")\n\n    if errors:\n        print(\"\\nFailed tests:\")\n        for err in errors:\n            print(f\"  {err}\")\n\n    sys.exit(0 if failed == 0 else 1)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":4788,"cache_read_input_tokens":39877,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":4788,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2083},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"4bb01819-f6f9-47d2-b75b-5c6d5fa9cd0b"}
