{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01N3pg6FHuPg6qxbRDNng8tP","type":"tool_result","content":"<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset='utf-8'><title>PetClinic :: Error</title><link rel='stylesheet' href='/webjars/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css'><link rel='stylesheet' href='/css/petclinic.css' /></head><body><nav class='navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark' role='navigation'><div class='container'><div class='navbar-header'><a class='navbar-brand' href='/app/'><span></span></a></div><div class='collapse navbar-collapse' id='main-navbar'><ul class='nav navbar-nav me-auto'><li class='active'><a href='/app/'><span class='fa fa-home'></span> Home</a></li><li><a href='/app/owners/find'><span class='fa fa-search'></span> Find Owners</a></li><li><a href='/app/vets.html'><span class='fa fa-th-list'></span> Veterinarians</a></li></ul></div></div></nav><div class='container-fluid'><div class='container xd-container'><h2>Welcome</h2><div class='row'><div class='col-md-12'><img class='img-responsive' src='/images/pets.png'/><h2>Error</h2><p>Something happened...</p><p>UT010023: Request HttpServletRequestImpl [ GET /app/vets.html ] was not original or a wrapper</p></div></div></div></div><script src='/webjars/bootstrap/5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js'></script></body></html>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"10a6e10b-2f8f-4b09-972c-f95c16cd253c"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01RgFXdWdZe5Kn1rkmcDgVdP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The error is `UT010023: Request HttpServletRequestImpl [ GET /app/owners ] was not original or a wrapper`. This is an Undertow error that occurs when trying to forward from a JAX-RS resource using `HttpServletRequest.getRequestDispatcher().forward()`. Undertow requires the original request wrapper, but JAX-RS injects a different request object.\n\nThis is a known issue with combining JAX-RS and Servlet forwarding in WildFly/RESTEasy. The `@Context HttpServletRequest` in JAX-RS gives a RESTEasy-wrapped request, not the original Undertow one.\n\nThe solution is to use `ServletContext.getRequestDispatcher()` instead of `HttpServletRequest.getRequestDispatcher()`, or to use `Response.seeOther()` for redirects, or to get the original request from the RESTEasy context. Let me check what works.\n\nActually, the proper solution in WildFly is to use `@Inject HttpServletRequest` via CDI instead of `@Context` for JAX-RS, or to change the approach. Let me try a different approach - use `jakarta.servlet.ServletContext` to get the dispatcher:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1109,"cache_read_input_tokens":104631,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1109,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1182},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"9b9815f7-538b-4aa2-915a-2ef942f0719b"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01RgFXdWdZe5Kn1rkmcDgVdP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_bdrk_01BJJLjkeCg6WU7zxYjERxBB","name":"Task","input":{"description":"Fix JSP forward in JAX-RS","prompt":"I need to fix a JSP forwarding issue in a WildFly/Jakarta EE application. The error is:\n`UT010023: Request HttpServletRequestImpl [ GET /app/owners ] was not original or a wrapper`\n\nThis happens when JAX-RS resource methods use `@Context HttpServletRequest request` and then call `request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/...\").forward(request, response)`.\n\nThe fix is needed in these files:\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/owner/OwnersResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/owner/PetResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/owner/VisitResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/vet/VetResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/system/WelcomeResource.java\n\nThe approach: In WildFly with RESTEasy, the `@Context HttpServletRequest` gives a wrapped request that Undertow won't accept for forwarding. The fix is to change the approach so that instead of using `void` return type with forward, we return a `Response` object or `StreamingOutput` that reads the JSP. OR, we can use `@Inject jakarta.servlet.ServletContext` and call `servletContext.getRequestDispatcher(path).forward(request, response)`.\n\nActually, the simplest and most reliable fix is:\n1. Add `@Inject jakarta.servlet.ServletContext servletContext;` to each resource\n2. Change all forward calls from `request.getRequestDispatcher(path).forward(request, response)` to `servletContext.getRequestDispatcher(path).forward(request, response)`\n\nIf that doesn't work, another approach is to have JAX-RS methods return the JSP view as a Viewable or use a different mechanism.\n\nPlease read each file, then apply the fix: add `@Inject jakarta.servlet.ServletContext servletContext;` and change all `request.getRequestDispatcher(...)` calls to `servletContext.getRequestDispatcher(...)` in all 5 files listed above. Make sure to add the import for `jakarta.servlet.ServletContext` if not present.","subagent_type":"general-purpose"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1109,"cache_read_input_tokens":104631,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1109,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1182},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"3c1a6a6d-af1f-4689-9a02-3244b8f28a93"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I need to fix a JSP forwarding issue in a WildFly/Jakarta EE application. The error is:\n`UT010023: Request HttpServletRequestImpl [ GET /app/owners ] was not original or a wrapper`\n\nThis happens when JAX-RS resource methods use `@Context HttpServletRequest request` and then call `request.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/...\").forward(request, response)`.\n\nThe fix is needed in these files:\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/owner/OwnersResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/owner/PetResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/owner/VisitResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/vet/VetResource.java\n- /home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__quarkus__jakarta/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/quarkus/samples/petclinic/system/WelcomeResource.java\n\nThe approach: In WildFly with RESTEasy, the `@Context HttpServletRequest` gives a wrapped request that Undertow won't accept for forwarding. The fix is to change the approach so that instead of using `void` return type with forward, we return a `Response` object or `StreamingOutput` that reads the JSP. OR, we can use `@Inject jakarta.servlet.ServletContext` and call `servletContext.getRequestDispatcher(path).forward(request, response)`.\n\nActually, the simplest and most reliable fix is:\n1. Add `@Inject jakarta.servlet.ServletContext servletContext;` to each resource\n2. Change all forward calls from `request.getRequestDispatcher(path).forward(request, response)` to `servletContext.getRequestDispatcher(path).forward(request, response)`\n\nIf that doesn't work, another approach is to have JAX-RS methods return the JSP view as a Viewable or use a different mechanism.\n\nPlease read each file, then apply the fix: add `@Inject jakarta.servlet.ServletContext servletContext;` and change all `request.getRequestDispatcher(...)` calls to `servletContext.getRequestDispatcher(...)` in all 5 files listed above. Make sure to add the import for `jakarta.servlet.ServletContext` if not present."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01BJJLjkeCg6WU7zxYjERxBB","session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"8fc4e5a1-fa79-45c0-8120-5bde86d465bd"}
