{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011MGQFwWPrXJKDCKYct5Hgn","type":"tool_result","content":"<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset='utf-8'><title>PetClinic :: Error</title><link rel='stylesheet' href='/webjars/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css'><link rel='stylesheet' href='/css/petclinic.css' /></head><body><nav class='navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark' role='navigation'><div class='container'><div class='navbar-header'><a class='navbar-brand' href='/app/'><span></span></a></div><div class='collapse navbar-collapse' id='main-navbar'><ul class='nav navbar-nav me-auto'><li class='active'><a href='/app/'><span class='fa fa-home'></span> Home</a></li><li><a href='/app/owners/find'><span class='fa fa-search'></span> Find Owners</a></li><li><a href='/app/vets.html'><span class='fa fa-th-list'></span> Veterinarians</a></li></ul></div></div></nav><div class='container-fluid'><div class='container xd-container'><h2>Welcome</h2><div class='row'><div class='col-md-12'><img class='img-responsive' src='/images/pets.png'/><h2>Error</h2><p>Something happened...</p><p>UT010023: Request HttpServletRequestImpl [ GET /app/owners/find ] was not original or a wrapper</p></div></div></div></div><script src='/webjars/bootstrap/5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js'></script></body></html>---\n<!doctype html><html><head><meta charset='utf-8'><title>PetClinic :: Error</title><link rel='stylesheet' href='/webjars/font-awesome/4.7.0/css/font-awesome.min.css'><link rel='stylesheet' href='/css/petclinic.css' /></head><body><nav class='navbar navbar-expand-lg navbar-dark' role='navigation'><div class='container'><div class='navbar-header'><a class='navbar-brand' href='/app/'><span></span></a></div><div class='collapse navbar-collapse' id='main-navbar'><ul class='nav navbar-nav me-auto'><li class='active'><a href='/app/'><span class='fa fa-home'></span> Home</a></li><li><a href='/app/owners/find'><span class='fa fa-search'></span> Find Owners</a></li><li><a href='/app/vets.html'><span class='fa fa-th-list'></span> Veterinarians</a></li></ul></div></div></nav><div class='container-fluid'><div class='container xd-container'><h2>Welcome</h2><div class='row'><div class='col-md-12'><img class='img-responsive' src='/images/pets.png'/><h2>Error</h2><p>Something happened...</p><p>UT010023: Request HttpServletRequestImpl [ GET /app/owners/new ] was not original or a wrapper</p></div></div></div></div><script src='/webjars/bootstrap/5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js'></script></body></html>","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"2b973449-5bf3-4d4e-9393-6f350b518092"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_0145XKCQm8AYEwkFvJgM1ur9","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Wait - those ALL fail too! So the smoke tests said 8 passed but those relied on the ErrorExceptionMapper catching the exception and returning 200. The smoke tests that \"passed\" are ones that only checked for status 200 without data assertions.\n\nEvery JSP forward fails. The `forward()` and `include()` approaches won't work with RESTEasy's wrapped request in Undertow.\n\nThe correct fix is to completely abandon JSP forwarding from JAX-RS and instead use one of these approaches:\n1. **Convert to plain Servlets** for HTML-rendering \n2. **Use JAX-RS `StreamingOutput`** - return a `Response` object that renders JSP via `RequestDispatcher.include()` into a `StreamingOutput`\n3. **Use a completely different template engine** (like Thymeleaf or Freemarker)\n\nThe most practical approach for minimal code change is to convert from JAX-RS with JSP forwarding to **plain Servlets** for HTML endpoints while keeping JAX-RS for JSON endpoints. But an even simpler approach: use `Response.temporaryRedirect()` to redirect to JSP URLs, but that won't allow passing attributes.\n\nLet me try the `StreamingOutput` approach - this way JAX-RS methods return a `Response` with the JSP content rendered via `include()`:\n\nActually, the real issue is that `forward()` and `include()` both need the original request. Let me try yet another approach: **use a Servlet Filter** that intercepts JAX-RS response and does the JSP rendering, or use **`@WebServlet` annotated servlets** for the HTML paths.\n\nThe most reliable approach is to switch from JSP to a template engine that doesn't require Servlet forwarding. **FreeMarker** or even **manual HTML generation** (like the ErrorExceptionMapper already does).\n\nLet me take the cleanest approach: **convert to Servlets**. The JAX-RS Application Path is `/app`, and I'll register Servlets at the same paths. But wait - having both Servlets and JAX-RS at `/app/*` would conflict.\n\nLet me think about the simplest working solution:\n\n1. Remove `@ApplicationPath(\"/app\")` \n2. Convert all HTML-rendering endpoints to `@WebServlet` classes\n3. Keep the JSON endpoints as JAX-RS resources at different paths\n\nActually, the SIMPLEST fix: let me try to configure RESTEasy to not wrap the servlet request. In WildFly, I can set the system property `resteasy.allow-forwarding=true` or configure RESTEasy differently.\n\nLet me try adding a `jboss-web.xml` configuration or a RESTEasy-specific fix:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1436,"cache_read_input_tokens":116401,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1436,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":721},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"0860f8d6-eb43-491d-992e-793a5e9d3933"}
