{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017beJQzxicC4LrB8NXcSzAC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.quarkus.samples.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.inject.Inject;\n     4→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n     5→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n     6→import jakarta.servlet.ServletContext;\n     7→import jakarta.servlet.ServletException;\n     8→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest;\n     9→import jakarta.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse;\n    10→import jakarta.ws.rs.GET;\n    11→import jakarta.ws.rs.Path;\n    12→import jakarta.ws.rs.Produces;\n    13→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.Context;\n    14→import jakarta.ws.rs.core.MediaType;\n    15→\n    16→import java.io.IOException;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→\n    19→@Path(\"/\")\n    20→public class VetResource {\n    21→\n    22→    @PersistenceContext\n    23→    EntityManager em;\n    24→\n    25→    @Inject\n    26→    ServletContext servletContext;\n    27→\n    28→    @Context\n    29→    private HttpServletRequest request;\n    30→\n    31→    @Context\n    32→    private HttpServletResponse response;\n    33→\n    34→    @GET\n    35→    @Path(\"/vets.html\")\n    36→    @Produces(MediaType.TEXT_HTML)\n    37→    public void showResourcesVetPage() throws ServletException, IOException {\n    38→        List<Vet> vets = em.createQuery(\"SELECT v FROM Vet v\", Vet.class).getResultList();\n    39→        request.setAttribute(\"vets\", vets);\n    40→        servletContext.getRequestDispatcher(\"/WEB-INF/jsp/vetList.jsp\").forward(request, response);\n    41→    }\n    42→\n    43→    @GET\n    44→    @Path(\"/vets\")\n    45→    @Produces(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON)\n    46→    public Vets showResourcesVetList() {\n    47→        Vets vets = new Vets();\n    48→        vets.getVetList().addAll(em.createQuery(\"SELECT v FROM Vet v\", Vet.class).getResultList());\n    49→        return vets;\n    50→    }\n    51→}\n    52→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"7f637c81-ad83-4bee-8ef2-75fe00dc3064"}
