{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_016VnQMqDebkJJEy6qd5zdmz","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Let me summarize the findings for you:\n\n1. WelcomeServlet.java: A servlet that forwards requests to /app or /app/ to the welcome.jsp page.\n2. CrashServlet.java: A servlet that intentionally throws a RuntimeException when accessed at /app/oups for error handling demonstration.\n3. OwnersServlet.java: A comprehensive servlet handling various owner-related operations like listing, finding, creating, and updating owners.\n4. VetsServlet.java: A simple servlet that retrieves and displays a list of veterinarians.\n5. JaxRsApplication.java: This file does not exist.\n6. OwnersResource.java: A JAX-RS resource that provides a REST endpoint to list all owners.\n7. ErrorExceptionMapper.java: An exception mapper that handles exceptions by generating an HTML error page.\n8. web.xml: Configuration file that sets up welcome file, error page, and JSP encoding.\n9. smoke.py: A comprehensive Python script for smoke testing the application, checking various endpoints and functionalities.\n10. index.jsp: A simple JSP that redirects to the /app/ context path.\n\nRegarding the specific files you asked about:\n- PetResource.java: Does not exist\n- VisitResource.java: Does not exist\n- WelcomeResource.java: Does not exist\n\nIs there anything specific you would like to know about these files or the project structure?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"18927158-45c8-4480-8025-21200db12286","uuid":"2e5f4878-5f0d-4e8e-9ad5-1945c415f414"}
